post_text: We have had several questions about who has to wear a mask while at school. All students Kindergarten through grade 12 must wear a mask or face covering while in school or on district property. There was some confusion in the governors mandate specifically when speaking about children age 5, this passage is referring to pre-kindergarten aged students. If a student is enrolled in Kindergarten they will be required to wear a mask or face covering.
text: We have had several questions about who has to wear a mask while at school. All students Kindergarten through grade 12 must wear a mask or face covering while in school or on district property. There was some confusion in the governors mandate specifically when speaking about children age 5, this passage is referring to pre-kindergarten aged students. If a student is enrolled in Kindergarten they will be required to wear a mask or face covering.

post_text:
We have had several questions about face covering options. Currently, the planning guide from the Minnesota Department of Health states that face shields may be used in the following situations:
 Among students in Kindergarten through grade 8, when wearing a face covering is problematic.
 By teachers (all grades), when wearing a face covering may impede the educational process.
 For staff, students, or visitors who cannot tolerate a face covering due to a developmental, medical, or behavioral health condition.
 For staff providing direct support student services, when a face covering impedes the service being provided.
For optimal protection, the face shield should extend below the chin anteriorly, to the ears laterally, and there should be no exposed gap between the forehead and the shield’s headpiece.

Here is a link to the document if you wish to read it for yourself:
https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/schools/k12planguide.pdf?fbclid=IwAR2OwAOi-DXuCVcBPfPJTCHXoi8Re4MD3j6LB3qSlWfFz9QemgqYMDT4Dqg

post_text: Falls Driving School for 6-12-20: Announcement regarding Falls Driving School: R.E. Friday, June 12- Class will be from 8.45 to 12.15. Upon completion, a discount of 10% is being offered to those students who successfully complete the class and would like to take the behind the wheel portion with Falls Driving School. If interested, please bring completed release forms and $180 (payable to Falls Driving School) to class on Friday. Students who are at least 15 years of age ARE NOT able to begin driving with their parents until they complete the written test with the state of MN. Testing locations are Grand Rapids, Bemidji and Duluth and require no appointment. If you have any further questions, please see Mr. Casareto.

post_text:
Did your child participate in free or reduced-price school meals? Because schools are closed, a new program can help provide a food benefit. Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.

Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text: Have you ever thought about serving on the International Falls School Board? Do you want to know how you can make a difference in the lives of our children and help shape their futures? Now more than ever good people are needed! If you'd like to learn what it takes to run for, and serve on the International Falls school board, current board members, administration in partnership with Community Education are hosting an informational "School Board Academy." Learn from current board members on what it takes and how to run for school board, how you can help serve your community in this vitally important work. The academy is scheduled for Thursday, June 25 at 6:00 p.m. in the IFHS library. Please enter through the main doors. Social distancing will be in place and we ask that you contact the Community Education office via phone (218)-283-2571 x1186 or email dmcgonigle@isd361.org to register. This is a free session. Snacks will be provided.

post_text: The post our swimmers have all been waiting for...the Open Swimming for the MORNING swimmers will begin again on Monday, June 8 at 6.30 a.m and will be open until 8:00 a.m. with several social distance guidelines in place. We will only allow one swimmer per lane, or up to three swimmers from one household per lane for 30 minute blocks. You must carry your punch card with you until further notice and please limit your use of the locker room facilities wherever possible. Unfortunately, we are NOT YET ABLE to provide open family swimming time. We expect to be able to again offer that service once the Governor has gone to Phase 3 of his Covid reopening plans. Please call the Community Education office to reserve your 30 minute open swimming blocks. The 6.30 a.m. to 7:00 a.m. block is currently reserved for our swimmers 65 and older.

NEXT YEARS 11th GRADE STUDENTS:
PSAT sign-up is now open for this year’s 10th grade students interested in taking the PSAT test next October 14th at 8:30 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. (Wednesday).

Students interested in taking the test need to email the counseling office to secure a testing spot. Spaces are limited so PSAT testing will be filled on a first come basis. The PSAT is a preparatory test for students looking to take the SAT the following year.

PSAT is also the only test to qualify a student for the National Merit Scholarship Qualifying Test (NMSQT). This year the PSAT is offered at no charge to the student.

Looking at photographer Gregg Segal’s work for inspiration, Falls High school artists in grades 8th-12th (and Mrs. Simon too!) created self portraits for their final project of the semester.

Student artists surrounding themselves with the items that they have kept near them this past quarter while at home and distance learning. They gathered items that they needed, that they used, that comforted, that entertained. The resulting portraits tell a story about the unique circumstance they were in.

This slideshow showcases only some of the gorgeous artwork that was born . . . we thought you’d like to see!

https://youtu.be/qpT_sacF-FM

post_text:
A huge shout out to Nikki Skifstad for the amazing Senior Bags! 💜💛 The kindness and generosity of this community is amazing!

https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=10163626566585707&id=905880706
shared_text:
Nikki Skifstad
May 21 at 2:59 PM ·

While picking up their cap and gowns today, the FHS Seniors received their gift bags from our fundraiser.

Each senior received a gift bag of items worth approximately $60. We were able to put $4600 back into the community and were able to spread those funds out between 10 different area businesses.

In addition, we received donated items from Molly French & Bob French (Pens By Bob), Cherie Serrano, Thunderbird Lodge, and the students at St. Thomas Aquinas Catholic School.

THANK YOU to everyone who contributed to this fundraiser, to those who supported it, and to those who offered a kind word or offered to help. While I know this gesture can’t make up for how their senior year was so suddenly upended, I hope it brought them some joy and put a smile on their faces. It was also a great way to put some money back into our small businesses during this chaotic time. I wish we could’ve supported every small business in our area, but I did my best to spread it around.

Thank you again!!! 💙💛

shared_text:
Koerter's Fuel
May 7 at 11:20 PM ·

ATTENTION: True North Express of International Falls has donated $2000 in gas to all the Janitors, Bus Drivers, Para's, Teachers, Cooks and Office Staff of ISD 361 and St. Thomas Aquinas School.

They want to thank you for your time and dedication to our students during this pandemic. We appreciate you delivering meals, watching other essential workers kids during the day, teaching online, disinfecting the schools, etc.

We are going to limit this to $20 in gas per person so we can try to reach as many people as possible. This will be FCFS and when we run out, we will be done.

Please pull up to our Full Service pumps near the building and stay in your car. Eric, Jordan, or Mark will come out and pump your gas for you. Please show them your employee badge, so they can mark down your name.

PLEASE SHARE THIS POST TO ANYONE YOU KNOW THAT WORKS AT THE ABOVE MENTIONED SCHOOLS.

Please Follow our Page to receive updates.

post_text:
💜💛Falls High School 2020 Prom~ "A Twist on the 20's"
It is with deep sadness and disappointment that we must announce the cancellation of any FHS supported prom related gatherings. We have given much thought and held on to hope that we could provide you with a grand march and/or dance, and for reasons beyond our control we will be unable to do so.
With that said…instead of canceling everything all together, we have chosen to go the “Virtual” route! Please take the time to get dressed up and get those creative juices flowing! And just so you know, all the wonderful donations for post prom prizes will now be drawn for any participating student!

Who~ Juniors and Seniors
What~ Virtual grand march for you and the public
When~ Saturday, June 13th
Where~ Any place allowed, following the
social distancing guidelines
Why~ To have the chance to get dressed up for all to see
and to make memories
How~ Take a photo or a short video (15 sec or less),
send it to us by June 5th

More info and details coming soon~ stay tuned!

Starting this week, WDIO will highlight students in northern Minnesota, Wisconsin and Michigan in their newscasts! These will be aired during the 5, 6 and 10 o'clock news.

Tune in to watch 2 of our Senior Salute messages:
May 6th - 6 PM News - Maddy Olson
May 12th - 10 PM News - Ben Skifstad

The Senior Salute messages will also be posted on the WDIO website and streaming app for anyone who may have missed it in their newscasts.

post_text:
Good afternoon,

This is Tim Everson from Falls High School asking you to complete a Distance Learning Family Survey. We now know that we will be continuing with distance learning for the remainder of the school year and we are reaching out to families to get feedback regarding our current distance learning delivery and your technology at home.



I have included a link below for our survey that I’m asking you to complete. I have also shared the link on the school’s Facebook page. We will be reviewing the results and making changes to try to make the distance learning instruction as successful as possible for both students and families in upcoming weeks.



Please feel free to contact us at any time if you have questions or problems accessing the curriculum or if you need additional devices. We want our students to be as successful as possible through this change of delivery.

Thank you,

Tim Everson



https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSecmpbCzeFDzu9H8FVrF5ewSHmPx6wAY-Hgqqx_FQ7iieZQIA/viewform?usp=sf_link

International Falls Public Schools, an equal opportunity employer, is seeking applications for the following position:

Elementary Licensed School Counselor or School Social
Worker

For school year 2020-2021, 1.0 FTE

Applications may be found at https://www.isd361.k12.mn.us/o/isd-361/page/employment-opportunities--605
and should include application form, resume, references, transcripts/credentials and a copy of your Minnesota professional license. Send materials by fax, email, or US mail to:

Falls High School
Attn: Jennifer Horne, Payroll/Employee Benefits
1515 11th Street
International Falls, MN 56649
Fax: (218) 283-2384
Email: jhorne@isd361.org

Deadline to apply is April 17, 2020 by 3:00p.m.
